    add(&quot;j);
}};
```

It&#39;s considered an anti-pattern **(depending on how you use it)**, but I still think there are some use cases where it is valid and **makes your life easier** (**tests, static configurations, manual constructing of JSON schemas, etc**).

You can read more about it here https://www.baeldung.com/java-double-brace-initialization

