You must create a fat JAR. 

The following Gradle task creates a fat JAR for a non modular project. Try to include it: 

    task createCustomFatJar(type: Jar) {
        manifest {
            attributes &#39;Main-Class&#39;: &quot;${mainClassNameParam}&quot;
        }
        duplicatesStrategy = DuplicatesStrategy.EXCLUDE
        from { configurations.runtimeClasspath.collect { it.isDirectory() ? it : zipTree(it) } }
        with jar
    }

If you do not need your project to be modular, you can download and alter this preconfigured project: 

https://github.com/davidweber411/SimpleJavaFxAppWithoutModules

**Working alternative:**

You can create a full working non modular Gradle JavaFX Project with this tool:

https://wedasoft.com/projects/javafx-project-generator/

Everything ist preconfigured and you just need to execute the Gradle task `createCustomFatJar` to create a fat JAR.

